The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Spain to host in 2006

Chennai: The Netherlands and Spain will host the Champions Trophy hockey tournaments for women and men, respectively, next year. 

Rome will host the womens World Cup qualifiers from April 26 to May 7, a press release by the FIH said Saturday. 

The executive board of the FIH, which met in Lausanne Friday, decided Amstelveen will host the July 8-16 (next year) womens Champions Trophy, while Terrassa (Spain) will host the mens Champions Trophy (July 22-30 next year). 

The 2007 edition hosts will be decided at the FIH executive board meeting in September. Chennai will be hosting the Champions Trophy this year. (PTI) 




